For your fastest pigeon.

14:00.229 --> 14:04.031
This absolutely, positively
has to be there overnight.

14:04.032 --> 14:07.835
You upheld your end of the
bargain, so I'll uphold mine.

14:07.837 --> 14:10.839
You have my permission to make
the most romantic of meals tonight

14:10.839 --> 14:12.406
for you and my hand maiden.

14:12.407 --> 14:14.375
Spare no expense...
Fresh oysters, braised rabbit,

14:14.376 --> 14:16.277
and a nice Bordeaux
from my private cellar.

14:16.278 --> 14:18.379
Oh, I don't even know if she'll say yes.

14:18.380 --> 14:21.782
I mean, we flirt and stuff,
but when I ask her on a date, bubkes.

14:21.783 --> 14:24.018
God, do I have to do everything
around here?

14:24.019 --> 14:25.853
Gwynne!

14:25.854 --> 14:28.289
You're having dinner tonight
with smallpox over here.

14:28.290 --> 14:30.191
Yes, m'lady.

14:30.192 --> 14:32.393
You two aren't cousins
or anything, are you?

14:32.394 --> 14:35.496
Ah, who cares? You guys couldn't
get any weirder looking.

14:40.535 --> 14:42.403
I know a hook-up from your boss

14:42.404 --> 14:44.839
isn't the smoothest thing, but...

14:44.840 --> 14:46.874
I don't care.

14:46.875 --> 14:50.211
Because, truthfully, I think
we could be great together.

14:50.212 --> 14:53.647
But love isn't meant for people like us.

14:53.648 --> 14:56.484
I beg to differ.

14:59.354 --> 15:04.191
♪ If I could share my life with you ♪

15:04.192 --> 15:08.195
♪ Just think how happy we'd be ♪

15:08.196 --> 15:12.266
♪ We'd share our hovel built for two ♪

15:12.267 --> 15:14.468
♪ Complete with vermin for three ♪

15:16.037 --> 15:20.007
♪ We could while away each hopeless day ♪

15:20.008 --> 15:23.377
♪ Comparing open sores ♪

15:23.378 --> 15:27.448
♪ Yes, life would blow,
but much less, though ♪

15:27.449 --> 15:30.718
♪ If I could share mine with yours ♪

15:30.719 --> 15:33.787
No, I can't. It's impossible!

15:33.788 --> 15:37.624
♪ If I could share my life with you ♪

15:37.625 --> 15:40.627
♪ Admit it, it would be nice ♪

15:40.628 --> 15:45.265
♪ We'd share one cot, one chamber pot ♪

15:45.266 --> 15:49.470
♪ Plus trench mouth, tapeworms, and lice ♪

15:49.471 --> 15:52.906
♪ We would have a dozen kids ♪

15:52.907 --> 15:57.377
♪ And maybe one won't die ♪

15:57.378 --> 15:58.545
♪ And the plague ♪

15:58.546 --> 15:59.646
♪ The runs ♪

15:59.647 --> 16:01.615
♪ Invading huns ♪

16:01.616 --> 16:05.219
♪ Just think how time would fly ♪

16:05.220 --> 16:09.056
♪ If you could share your life with me ♪

16:09.057 --> 16:13.026
♪ I'll Cherish every foul breath ♪

16:13.027 --> 16:14.995
- ♪ The filth ♪
- ♪ The rot ♪

16:14.996 --> 16:17.264
♪ The leprosy ♪

16:17.265 --> 16:21.034
♪ The painful, lingering death ♪

16:21.035 --> 16:25.205
♪ Thank the Lord our life expectancy ♪

16:25.206 --> 16:27.974
♪ Is merely 32 ♪

16:30.178 --> 16:35.182
♪ Yeah, it might be sweet misery ♪

16:35.183 --> 16:46.325
♪ To share what's left with yo-o-o-u ♪

16:46.327 --> 16:50.730
So, me, you, dinner tonight, my place.

16:50.731 --> 16:52.332
You bring that pretty
little smile of yours,

16:52.333 --> 16:54.100
and I'll supply the rest.

16:54.101 --> 16:56.369
Yes!

17:06.414 --> 17:10.183
Right, princess. You ready
to get your kingdom back?

17:10.184 --> 17:11.818
I've been thinking.

17:11.819 --> 17:14.054
I can get another kingdom.
It's a buyer's market right now.

17:14.055 --> 17:15.521
Let's just free my parents,

17:15.522 --> 17:16.723
get Madalena, and get us out of here.

17:16.723 --> 17:17.891
Absolutely not.

17:17.892 --> 17:20.492
When I make a promise, I keep it.

17:20.493 --> 17:22.028
We're gonna get your kingdom back.

17:22.029 --> 17:23.396
- But...
- Once the concert starts,

17:23.396 --> 17:25.732
we're gonna have about an hour
to move about the castle.

17:25.733 --> 17:27.133
Where do you think
they're keeping your parents?

17:27.134 --> 17:31.070
Perhaps they're up your butt.

17:31.071 --> 17:34.174
Y-you see, because
that's the most unlikely place.

17:34.175 --> 17:37.409
I mean, obviously, her parents
couldn't be up your...

17:37.411 --> 17:39.245
Well, well, well.

17:39.246 --> 17:41.714
Ah, it's too late.
I had to go for the stupid butt joke.

17:41.715 --> 17:43.616
Forget it. Guards, just seize them.

17:51.458 --> 17:52.892
Your move...

17:52.893 --> 17:54.961
'Cause I haven't killed anybody all day.

17:54.962 --> 17:57.363
Gareth, we agreed
<i>I</i> would say the cool things.

17:57.364 --> 18:00.428
- So, what's it gonna be?
- Damn it, Gareth!

18:01.607 --> 18:02.769
Fine.

18:02.770 --> 18:04.036
Galavant, no!

18:04.037 --> 18:05.705
Now let her go.

18:05.706 --> 18:07.507
She had nothing to do with this.

18:07.508 --> 18:10.443
You are <i> so</i> noble.

18:10.444 --> 18:12.111
And yet the women in your life

18:12.112 --> 18:13.880
never seem to honor that nobility.

18:13.881 --> 18:17.083
In fact, this one tricked you
into coming all the way here

18:17.084 --> 18:18.518
so I could kill you.

18:21.555 --> 18:22.588
What?

18:23.957 --> 18:26.726
Well, well, well...

18:26.727 --> 18:29.462
Looks like it's time for dinner.

18:29.463 --> 18:32.264
- Nailed it.
- Boom.

18:35.254 --> 18:39.087
But... what the... all that time...

18:39.089 --> 18:41.157
He may not be able to talk, but I can.

18:41.158 --> 18:42.792
This is messed up, princess!

18:42.794 --> 18:44.962
I didn't have a choice.
He was going to kill my parents.

18:44.962 --> 18:46.162
Shut up!

18:47.498 --> 18:50.800
Well, seems like you kids
have lots to talk about.

18:50.801 --> 18:52.702
I'll let you get to it.

18:52.703 --> 18:54.137
Oh, but do hurry.

18:54.138 --> 18:56.606
I'm executing Galavant in 10 minutes. Hmm.

18:56.607 --> 18:59.342
It's nice to finally
have people down here.

18:59.343 --> 19:00.810
Feels lived in.

19:00.811 --> 19:04.180
I'm so sorry.
I wanted to tell you, but I...

19:04.181 --> 19:06.315
But what?

19:06.316 --> 19:08.139
You didn't have time?

19:08.185 --> 19:09.886
Not in the hundreds of miles we traveled

19:09.887 --> 19:11.587
or the meals we shared?

19:11.588 --> 19:15.858
In retrospect, the trip
through the forest of honesty

19:15.859 --> 19:17.360
would have seemed like
an appropriate time.

19:17.361 --> 19:18.928
But my family.

19:18.929 --> 19:22.699
Well, perhaps if you'd told me,
we could have made a plan.

19:22.700 --> 19:24.834
And you would have helped me?

19:24.835 --> 19:26.969
Even if you had nothing to gain from it?

19:26.970 --> 19:30.907
I guess we'll never find out.

19:33.377 --> 19:35.778
If even a single ounce of you was real,

19:35.779 --> 19:37.346
just tell me one thing...

19:37.347 --> 19:39.282
Did Madalena want me to come for her?

19:39.283 --> 19:41.584
I don't know.

19:45.389 --> 19:46.522
No!

20:09.212 --> 20:11.814
Not so tough, are you now,

20:11.815 --> 20:12.848
Galavan...

20:14.198 --> 20:15.084
Aah!!

20:15.085 --> 20:17.186
Aah!!

20:23.794 --> 20:26.595
Hello, darling.

20:26.596 --> 20:28.097
Madalena?

20:29.700 --> 20:34.103
There's braised rabbit
and Bordeaux, your favorites.

20:34.104 --> 20:36.739
<i>You</i> saved me?

20:36.740 --> 20:38.707
Oh, I've done a lot more than that.

20:44.347 --> 20:46.482
We have a lot of catching up to do.

20:48.433 --> 20:51.153
I've written someone,

20:51.154 --> 20:53.856
and he's coming to execute my plan.

20:53.857 --> 20:55.758
He doesn't play nice.

20:59.362 --> 21:01.515
Everything's about to change.

